column32: People have worn out "performative." We often perform things that are real, you know. Posting is a kind of performance of one's politics. Performative doesn't actually mean "fake" or "empty," it just gets deployed that way. We actually need performance. Case in point: last night's performance.

It would be nice if we could have a PM who lasts more than a few months, frankly. Dunno about you lot, but I am tired of politics being a constant exhausting drama driven by hot takes, newsletter posts, lobby corrs interviewing other lobby corrs, gossip and memes.

Please don't accuse people in knitted hats of only wearing their supposed politics if all you're doing is posting, which is basically just another way of wearing your politics. It's a silly thing to attack people over in any case. Using fashion to signal support for ongoing acts of rebellion is good

Keir Starmer is a good, decent man with public service running through his veins. He came into politics for all the right reasons. He‚Äôs defied the naysayers many times and he‚Äôll do so again. He‚Äôs changing and renewing our country and has restored it‚Äôs reputation across the world.

column56:
[{'alt': 'an encyclopedia eorzea style entry that reads:

ANNETTE LEVEILLEUR

"My schedule can always accommodate the company of a friend!"

One of the brightest young ladies to have graced Sharlayan throughout multiple generations, Annette Leveilleur upholds her family named with aplomb. The oft times particular politics of Sharlayan society are no match for her as she wields her father's grace and her mother's warmth like a perfectly sharpened sword.

When not dazzling amongst her peers, Annette much prefers the company of Aetherological tomes and the occasional rendezvous with a figure clad in black robes in the odd comfort of the Aitiascope.. Researchers in Labyrinthos may be fooled by her quick thinking in her unauthorized visits to the edges of the Atherial Sea, her movements are always under the watchful eye of her mother - regardless of her being physically present or otherwise.

Despite these more strange past-times, Annette endeavors to keep them a secret so that she can enjoy as much of normal teenage life as possible. Ribbon shopping at the Agora so that she can match with her friends at tea, searching for deeper meaning in poetry from across the salt, or simply spending time doing anything that is not saving the Star from imminent danger like her parents once did.', 'aspectRatio': {'height': 1318, 'width': 2000}, 'image': {'$type': 'blob', 'ref': {'$link': 'bafkreiawt36nol7hzl6ie2djhzwxwqwmjsecehc6zkif7czg6xgdkbckou'}, 'mimeType': 'image/jpeg', 'size': 786246}}, {'alt': 'an encyclopedia eorzea style entry that reads:

ARTHUR LEVEILLEUR

"Life is a lot more interesting when you realize it isn't just you living it."

The youngest, and only, son of the vaulted Warrior of Light and the current Lord Leveilleur, Arthur has spent much of his life feeling societal pressure on who he is to be. A scholar, a swordsman, or perhaps even a man of the state ‚Äî many wonder exactly which he will choose to pursue as he comes of age.

Admitted to the Studium just on the cup of his fourteenth Summer, the realization that the life of a traditional scholar was one he did not wish for was the catalyst for his short lived disappearance toOthard. While caught mere moments after setting foot on the docks of Doma by his maternal grandfather, Mikos, this did not dissuade him from his course. The boy returned to Sharlayan free from the curse of apathy and blessed with a hunger for seeing the world. With permission, Arthur currently spends his days alongside his grandfather as they traverse Othard's myriad landscapes.

Deeply moved by the kindness of the people he has encountered, Arthur has found that he has a perfect way to remember every last one of them. With his father's old charcoals and handmade paints crafted from only the Twelve knows what, Arthur has taken to painting portraits of those who he meets along his travels. Little does he know, his father is particularly proud of this new creative outlet.', 'aspectRatio': {'height': 1318, 'width': 2000}, 'image': {'$type': 'blob', 'ref': {'$link': 'bafkreicdyl2bqtvnlndk46vxziyad62itlhghdewtkot4uhq6lq5j4njby'}, 'mimeType': 'image/jpeg', 'size': 862412}}]
